                        "key": "westonpace",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34045",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34045"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Weston Pace",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "If I understand the response from Valgrind correctly the statement \"Apparently valgrind will instrument the CPU feature flags when you run under valgrind, and it would should AVX512 is not supported, and so pyarrow should avoid using it\" is not quite correct.\r\n\r\nThe CPU supports vmovdqa64 / AVX512.  Valgrind does not support this.  Arrow does not check which flags Valgrind supports when compiling (presumably most users are not going to use Valgrind and would rather have the better performance).\r\n\r\nSo at the moment I think it's pretty acceptable to say \"If a developer is going to use Valgrind then the burden is on the developer to ensure they manually specify Arrow does not use AVX512\".\r\n\r\nPerhaps this is something we could add to our C++ development docs.  We could maybe raise a JIRA for a new CMake option \"valgrind compatibility\" which disables AVX512.  There is already a (perhaps hidden / not-documented) flag ARROW_TEST_MEMCHECK which disables a number of tests that are not \"valgrind friendly\" but I think that is an orthogonal issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=westonpace",
                        "name": "westonpace",
                        "key": "westonpace",
                        "avatarUrls": {
