                    "body": "Coming back tot his issue, it seems its still not resolved ( although I can work around it now by setting the SIMD env var ).\r\nLooking at the code now, I believe there is a bug when checking CPU flags.  The #if/#elif/#ifndef checks seem off, and on linux the flags are never getting set:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/d056829e877cdbbe071ea3fb34bd0b9ad42145e6/cpp/src/arrow/util/cpu_info.cc#L439\r\n\r\nThis line should supposedly check the flags on non-ARM CPUs, but its under an #if _WIN32 block.  \r\nI don\u2019t see any code path that checks CPU flags on linux.\r\n\r\n",
